The oldest known stone javelins have been discovered in Africa, predating humans by 80,000 years.

The discovery of the 280,000-year-old spear tips means that they were probably created by ancestors to ancient humans, rather than by our species.

This discovery means Homo heidelbergensis, our ancestor, was much more technologically advanced than previously thought.

